The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, July 25, 2005

 Poetry

 Lost and Found, the second reading session of Fringe Poetry: A festival of Verse at Oxford Bookstore, 6 pm.

 Fair

 Kitchenex 2005, an exhibition-cum-sale of kitchenware and home appliances, at Ice Skating Rink.

 On display

 Creations of a collaborative workshop with traditional and contemporary artists on display at CIMA Gallery, 3 pm to 7 pm.

 An exhibition of Bishnu De?s collection of folk art at Bangiya Sahitya Parishat, 2 pm to 6 pm.

 Kaleidoscope, an exhibition of collage paintings by Indrani Sen, will be opened at Academy of Fine Arts, 6 pm.

 Photographs by Ashish Avikunthak on view at Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 Tribute

 A programme to celebrate the 167th birth anniversary of Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay at Bhasha Bhavan, 4 pm.

 Soiree

 Classical music recitals by Pandit Shyamal Chattopadhayay (sitar), Prabir Banerjee (vocal) and Nisha Jaiswal (bhajan), to mark the 125th birth anniversary of Munsi Prem Chand, at Gorky Sadan, 5.45 pm.

 Workshop

 A workshop for women on folk painting of Orissa, West Bengal and Bihar at Bharatiyam, 11 am to 5 pm.




